data.text:
This is a fan cast of Syphon Filter 2. It is based on the characters from the Syphon Filter 2 (2000) game.

If you want to read about Soldier of Fortune Inc. actors and actresses, visit this page: https://gamesandmoviesblog.wordpress.com/syphon-filter-soldier-of-fortune-inc/ – On this page I also discussed the similarities between Syphon Filter and Soldier of Fortune Inc.

Note: The pictures which are used for this blog belong to their owners.

Here is a cover photo, which I created for the Syphon Filter fan cast

Yunjin Kim as Lian Xing and Brad Johnson as Gabe Logan. Yunjin’s picture is from the TV show Lost and Brad’s photo is from the TV show Soldier of Fortune Inc.

Below is the same photo without title. If you want to see this photo in full size, just click it.

Syphon Filter 2

Cast

Brad Johnson – Gabe Logan

Brad Johnson was born on October 24, 1959. He is an American actor. His most notable role was Matt Sheppard in Soldier of Fortune Inc. He is also known for Always (1989), Nam Angels (1989), Fight of the Intruder (1991), Philadelphia Experiment II (1993), The Birds II: Land’s End (1994), Cries Unheard: The Donna Yaklich Story (1994), Stringo (1995), Across the Line (2000), Crossfire Trail (2001), Riverworld (2003), No Regrets (2004),Wild Things: Diamonds in the Rough (2005), Alien Siege (2005), Truce (2005), Safe Harbour (2007), Copperhead (2008) and etc. He has six daughters and four sons.

Brad Johnson’s photos

Yunjin Kim – Lian Xing

Yunjin Kim was born on November 7, 1973. She is a South Korea-born American film and theater actress. She is best known for her role as Sun in Lost (TV series 2004-2010) and as the North Korean spy Bang-Hee in the South Korean film Shiri. Also she is known for Ardor (2002), Diary of June (2005), Seven Days (2007), Mistresses (2013), Ode to My Father (2014) and etc. In 2008 Yunjin voiced Sun Kwan in the Lost: Via Domus video game.

Yunjin Kim’s photos

Manuela Arcuri – Teresa Lipan

Manuela Arcuri (Emmanuela Arcuri) was born on January 8, 1977 in Anagni Lazio, Italy. Manuela is one of the most beautiful Italian women. She is an actress, model and a television presenter. She began her modeling career at the age of 15. She posed as a photo-model for many magazines. In 1995 she played in Black holes (Original title: I buchi neri) and it was her first movie. Since then she has played in many movies, TV series and theater roles. In 2000 she appeared in a calendar for the magazine Gente Viaggi and Italian Playboy. The following year Manuela posed for another calendar for the magazine Panorama. In 2001 Manuela played a role of Paola Vitali in Carabinieri (TV series 2001-2002). In 2005 she played Paola Vitali in Carabinieri: Sotto Copertura. Manuela Arcuri is known for Mad Love (2001) (Original title: Juana la locca and Italian title: Giovanna la pazza), The Watch Affair (2003) (Original title: Cosa de brujas and Italian title: La notte delle streghe) and etc. She also played in some theater roles, for instance, Liolà (2006), Il primo che mi capita (2008), A pretty story of woman (2010). In 2003 she had a long relationship with Francesco Coco, who was born on the same day, the same month and the same year as Arcuri. She also had a relationship with an Italian fencer Aldo Montano in 2006. Since 2010 she is engaged with a developer Giovanni Di Gianfrancesco and in October 2013 Manuela announced that she was pregnant. On May 8, 2014 she had a son named Matthew. Manuela has two brothers Sergio and Marco.

I also chose Manuela for Jill Valentine’s character in Resident Evil Fan cast

Visit this page if you are interested in Resident Evil Fan Cast: https://gamesandmoviesblog.wordpress.com/resident-evil-fan-cast/

Manuela Arcuri’s photos

Manuela Arcuri in Carabinieri

Manuela Arcuri with her husband Giovanni di Gianfrancesco and their child Mattia

Gary Swanson – Lyle Stevens

Gary Swanson was born on September 1, 1948. He is an American actor and a producer. He is known for Vice Squad (1982), Sniper (1993), Bone Collector (1999), Pate (2001), Nursie (2004), Whiskey School (2005), Trooper (2010) and etc. In 2010 he voiced two characters Carls Stucky and Deputy in Alan Wake (Video Game 2010).

Nicole Mary Kidman – Elsa Weissinger

Nicole Mary Kidman was born on June 20, 1967. She is an Australian actress and a film producer. She plays in movies and TV shows. Her first major role was Rae Ingram in Dead Calm (1989). The same year, she played Katrina Stanton in Bangkok Hilton (TV Mini-series 1989). She is known for Days of Thunder (1990), Far and Way (1992), Batman Forever (1995), Eyes Wide Shut (1999), Moulin Rouge (2001), The Others (2001), The Hours (2002) and etc. She played in Stoker (2013), Before I go to Sleep (2014), Secret in Their Eyes (2015), Genius (2016), and in many other movies. In 2016 she did voice acting in a cartoon – The Guardian Brothers.

Nicole Kidman’s photos

Russell Wong – Steven Archer

Russell Girard Wong was born on March 1, 1963. He is an American actor. He is the brother of an actor /model Michael Wong. He plays in movies, TV Shows, video games and etc. He is known for New Jack City (1991), Romeo Must Die (2000), Snow Flower and the Secret Fan (2011). In 2008 he played a role of Ming Guo in The Mummy : Tomb of the Dragon Emperor. Nowadays he continues acting in films and TV Shows.

Bob Gunton – Dillon Morgan

Robert Patrick “Bob” Gunton, Jr. was born on November 15, 1945. He is an American actor. In 1993 he played Chief George Earle in Demolition Man. He is known for The Shawshank Redemption (1994), where he played Warden Samuel Norton, Broken Arrow (1996), Patch Adams (1998), 24 (TV Series 2007-2010), Daredevil (TV Series 2015) and etc.

Sophia Crawford – Mara Aramov

Sophia Crawford was born on May 19, 1966 in Hammersmith, London, England, UK. Sophia is an actress, stuntwoman and martial artist. She was Sara Michelle Gellar’s stunt double on the first season of Buffy the Vampire Slayer. She married ‘Buffy’ stunt Co-ordinator, Jeff Pruitt in 1998. Sophia is known for many movies and TV series: The Vengance (1995), Mightly Morphin Power Rangers (TV series 1993-1995), WMAC Masters (TV Series 1996) and etc. Her most notable role was Sophia in U.S. Seals II (2001). She also doubled for Fergie in the 2006 movies Poseidon.

Other photos, which I created. If you want to see these photos in full size, just click them.

Sophia Crawford’s photos

Wade Williams – Uri Gregorov

Wade Williams was born on December 24, 1961. He is an American actor, who is best known for the role of Brad Bellick in television series Prison Break (TV Series 2005-2008). In 1998 he played Arnold Struel in the episode Brother’s keeper of NYPD Blue TV Series. In 1990’s he played many roles in various TV Series. He is also known for The Bernie Mac Show (TV Series 2001-2005), Collateral (2004), The Dark Knight Rises (2012), Gangster Squad (2013) and etc. Wade Williams did the voice acting for a video game Hitman Blood Money (2006) and also voiced Arkansas Dave Rudabaugh in Gun (Video Game 2005). In this game he did some additional voices too.

Esai Morales – Jason Chance

Esai Manuel Morales, Jr. Was born on October 1, 1962. He is an American actor. He plays in movies, TV Series, video games and short films. In 1994 he played a role of Sgt. Stern in the Army Now. He is known for La bamba (1987), Rapa Nui (1994), NYPD Blue (2001-2004), Gun Hill Road (2011) and etc. Esai did a voice over role of Captain Victor “Vic” Navarro in True Crime: New York City (Video Game 2005). In 2009-2010 he played Joseph Adama in Caprica (TV Series). In 2013-2015 he played Section Chief Mateo Cruz in Criminal Minds (TV Series).

Adewale Akinnuoye-Agbaje – Dr. Lawrence Mujari

Adewale Akinnuoye – Agbaje was born on 22 August in 1967. He is an English actor and a former fashion model. He is best known for his roles as Lock-Nah in The Mummy Returns (2001), Nykwana Wombos in The Bourne Identity (2002), Mr Eko on Lost (2005-2006), and Simon Adebisi on Oz ( TV Series 1997-2000). He is also known for G. I. Joe: The Rise of Cobra (2009), Thor: The Dark World (2013). He continues acting in various movies and TV Shows.

Olivier Martinez – John Ramirez

Olivier Martinez was born on January 12, 1966. He is a French actor. He became known after he played in several French films such as Un, deux, trois, soleil (1993), The Horseman on the Roof (1995), and The Chambermaid on the Titanic (1997). He is also known for Hollywood movies, for example: Before Night Falls (2000), the erotic thriller Unfaithful (2002), SWAT (2003), Taking Lives (2004), The Physician (2013) and etc.

Robert Taylor – Thomas Holman

Robert Taylor was born 1963. He is an Australian actor. He has appeared in many films and Television Series in Australia, the UK and the USA. He is known for The Feds movie series, The Last Bullet (1995), Vertical Limit (2000), Focus (2015), Longmire (2012-2016) and etc. His most notable role was Agent Jones in The Matrix (1999).

Matt McColm – Derrek Falkan

Matt McColm was born on January 31, 1965. He is an American actor, stuntman and a former model. He is known for Red Scorpion 2 (1994), Nightman (1997), Nightman (TV Series 1997-1999), Baywatch (TV Series 1991-2001). He played Agent Thomson in Matrix: Reloaded (2003), the same year he voiced his character in Enter the Matrix (Video Game 2003). He is also known for Cellular (2004), Terminator: The Sarah Connor Chronicles (TV Series 2008), Knight Rider (TV Series 2009) and etc.

Leon Russom as Vincent Hadden

Leon Russom was born on December 6, 1941. Russom has appeared in numerous television shows, particularly soap operas. He portrayed Admiral Toddman (in the Star Trek: Deep Space Nine episode “The Die is Cast”) and the Starfleet Commander-in-Chief in Star Trek VI: The Undiscovered Country. He also plays in movies. Leon is known for Another World ( TV Series 1976 – 1980), Mission Impossible (TV Series 1971), TV 101 ( TV Series 1988 – 1989), Double Dragon (1994), Childhood Sweetheart? (TV Movie 1997), The Big Lebowski ( TV Movie 1998), JAG (TV Series 1997-2002), NCIS (TV Series 2004), NYPD Blue (TV Series 1995-2004), Cold Case (TV Series 2006), True Grit (TV Movie 2010), and etc.

His most notable role were General Jonathan Kranz (Padman) in Prison Break (TV Series 2006-2009) and the Malibu police chief in The Big Lebowski.
